# Coding standard

Full detail: `.playbook/04_CODING_STANDARD.md`, `.playbook/10_COMPONENT_LIBRARY.md`.

- Vanilla JS + hand-written CSS (`assets/css/site.css`) only. No framework/CSS CDN. No new dependency without a DR in `12_DECISIONS.md`.
- All render methods on `Render` in `assets/js/render.js` — never bare top-level functions in `index.html`.
- Escape interpolated text/attrs via `Render.escapeHtml()`; chapter `body` is intentional raw HTML (never escape).
- Render functions are pure: args in → markup out; no `fetch()`; don’t reach outer state if it can be a parameter.
- After `Render` method changes: `node scripts/verify-render.js`.
- No content hardcoded in HTML/JS — edit `data/*.json` instead.
